statements: SELECT id, source_table, extraction_time FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE source_database = 'Sales' ORDER BY extraction_time DESC;
SELECT * FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE id = 10;
SELECT source_database, count(*) as record_count FROM etl_pipeline_data GROUP BY source_database;
SELECT * FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE transformation_script ILIKE '%cleaning%' ORDER BY id;
SELECT id, transformed_data FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE load_status = true ORDER BY id LIMIT 5;
SELECT id, source_database, source_table, extraction_time, transformed_data FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE source_database = 'sales' AND load_status = TRUE ORDER BY extraction_time DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT id, source_database, source_table, extraction_time, transformation_script FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE load_status = FALSE
SELECT * FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE source_database IN ('marketing','human_resources') ORDER BY id ASC LIMIT 5
SELECT id, source_database, source_table FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE extraction_time BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2021-06-30'
SELECT id, source_database, source_table, transformed_data FROM etl_pipeline_data WHERE transformed_data->>'total_sales' > '50000' ORDER BY id DESC
SELECT * FROM Extraction;
SELECT extracted_data FROM Transformation WHERE id = 5;
SELECT transformed_data, transformed_at FROM Transformation ORDER BY transformed_at DESC;
SELECT id, extracted_data, extracted_at FROM Extraction WHERE extracted_data LIKE '%example%';
SELECT id, extracted_data, extracted_at FROM Extraction ORDER BY extracted_data ASC, extracted_at DESC;
SELECT * FROM Extraction;

SELECT extracted_data, transformed_data FROM Transformation WHERE transformed_data ->> 'category' = 'finance' ORDER BY transformed_at DESC;
SELECT extracted_at, COUNT(id) AS total_records FROM Extraction GROUP BY extracted_at HAVING COUNT(id) > 5;
SELECT id, extracted_data, transformed_data FROM Transformation WHERE transformed_data -> 'details' ->> 'type' = 'invoice' LIMIT 10;

SELECT source_table, status FROM etl_extract WHERE status = 'failed' ORDER BY source_table ASC;

SELECT transformed_data, model_name FROM transformed_data JOIN machine_learning_model ON transformed_data.id = machine_learning_model.id

SELECT prediction_value, model_name FROM prediction_results JOIN machine_learning_model ON prediction_results.sample_id = machine_learning_model.id

SELECT * FROM ETL_Extract;
SELECT id, source_table FROM ETL_Extract WHERE extract_date = '2022-01-01';
SELECT transformed_data FROM ETL_Transform WHERE extract_id = 123 ORDER BY transform_date DESC;
SELECT model_name, model_type FROM ML_Model WHERE trained_date > '2021-01-01' AND trained_date < '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM ETL_Load WHERE load_date < '2022-01-01' ORDER BY transform_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM ETL_Extract WHERE extract_date = '2022-01-01';
SELECT id, source_table FROM ETL_Extract WHERE id < 100 ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT * FROM ETL_Load JOIN ETL_Transform ON ETL_Load.transform_id = ETL_Transform.id WHERE ETL_Transform.id IN (1, 3, 5) ORDER BY load_date DESC;
SELECT model_name, trained_date FROM ML_Model WHERE model_type = 'Regression';

SELECT ML_Model.model_name, ML_Prediction.prediction_data FROM ML_Model JOIN ML_Prediction ON ML_Model.id = ML_Prediction.model_id WHERE ML_Prediction.prediction_date > '2022-06-01' ORDER BY ML_Model.id ASC;
